# Template for the local-only env overrides used by Path B in
# docs/testing-on-phone.md (tunneled phone testing).
#
# To use:
#   cp .env.local.example .env.local
#
# The copied file (`.env.local`) is gitignored (matches *.local).
#
# The VITE_BACKEND_URL line below is commented out by default so the
# file can sit on disk during normal dev without overriding anything.
# Uncomment it when you start a tunneling session — empty value forces
# the API client to build relative URLs, which routes through the Vite
# proxy in vite.config.local.ts. Re-comment when you're back to plain
# `npm run dev`.
#VITE_BACKEND_URL=
